Oman: Oman, Dhofar: foothills of the Jabal Qara along the track between Raysut and Qaftawt, stony slopes with open Commiphora - woodland, alt. 100 m, 17°02'N, 53°55'E. Slopes with woodland, strongly grazed by camels, and dense grassland. Alt.: 100 m. 3.10.1998, Leg.: P. Hein & N. Kilian PH 5136.

Yemen: Socotra. limestone plateau delimiting western Nogat plain inlands, c. 10 km E of Ras Katanahan. Wadis and depressions of the plateau. Alt.: 520 m. 18.3.2003, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. A. Hubaishan YP 4176.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. Northern Fartak Mts, dissected table-land near the track W below J. Karmoum (with the disused radio tower). Relevé A27: Rocky slope (incl. 25°) with small rock ledges, dwarf shrub vegetation dominating. Alt.: 600-650 m. 8.10.2001, Leg.: P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. Reisch YP 1082c.

Yemen: Socotra. Ma'ala plateau, westernmost ascent from Wadi Galansia, limestone. Relevé A101: N-exp. rocky slope (incl. 5-10°), rich deciduous Sterculia - Lannea transulta woodland (tree layer to 7 m, shrub layer to 4 m tall, dense herbal layer). Alt.: 330 m. 8.3.2003, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & H. Kürschner YP 3809.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Al Mukalla - Sayun main road, broad wadi S of the Jol escarpment, S of the village Abdallah Karib. Sandy wadi flat with therophyte vegetation between scattered shrubs (2 weeks after heavy rains). Alt.: 180 m. 10.11.1999, Leg.: P. Hein, M. Al-Mashjary & N. Kilian PH 6208.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. track between Al Ghaida and Hawf, mountain ridge 20 km E of Al Faydami, S/SW- resp. sea-exposed rocky slopes and cliffs, catching the humidity of the monsoon mist. Dense green vegetation with small shrubs and annuals. Alt.: 50-250 m. 26.9.1998, Leg.: P. Hein, S. A. Ghazanfar & N. Kilian PH 4989.

Yemen: Gov. Abyan. Jabal Urays, middle Wadi Asurie, Sterculia africana zone. Relevé A51: W-exposed slope (incl. 20°) with huge rocks, open woodland with scattered old Sterculia trees (trunk diam. 1.5-2 m), tree layer 2-10 m, shrub layer to 2 m tall. Alt.: 550-650 m. 17.3.2002, Leg.: P. Hein & H. Kürschner YP 1789.

Yemen: Gov. Hadhramout. Jol, road from Seyun to Mukalla, 30 km N Ras Howeirah (20 km S Wadi Ayn). Depression in the otherwise stony plateau, with alluvial loamy and silty soil. Alt.: 1230 m. 18.10.2001, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein & H. Kürschner YP 1299.

El Salvador: Depto. Santa Ana, Mpio. Chalchuapa, calle Ramón Flores oriente, entrada al estadio El Progreso (modelo) . Vegetación en Area urbana/orilla de la calle. Hierba cespitosa con espiguillas casi blancas . Alt.: 718 m.2019-05-19, Leg.: Rodríguez,D. & Molina,A. 7338 [DR-07338].
Yemen: Hadhramout. 20 km NE of Ghayl Ba Wazir, lower Wadi Barras S of the Wadi Arf gorge. Alt.: 100-200 m. 31.10.2000, Leg.: N. Kilian, S. M. A. . Bashmeilah, P. Hein & M. A. Hubaishan NK 6564b.

Yemen: Socotra. track from the N coast inlands to Galansia, N facing slope of saddle between the northern coastal plain and Wadi Galansia. Croton socotranus woodland on limestone. Alt.: c. 250 m. 5.3.2003, Leg.: N. Kilian, P. Hein, H. Kürschner & M. A. Hubaishan YP 3666.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. below Shahrut. Relevé A69: SE-exp. slope (incl. 15-20°) with open Acacia-Commiphora-Anogeissus woodland, tree layer to 4 m, shrub layer to 2 m tall, dense herbal layer. Alt.: 380 m. 24.8.2002, Leg.: P. Hein YP 3011.
